snippet: An icy clash between Gov. Mark Dayton, a Democrat, and Republican lawmakers shows the politics involved in a crucial element of the new federal health care law.
abstract: Standoff between Minnesota Gov Mark Dayton, a Democrat, and state Republican lawmakers over setting up a health insurance marketplace for people who do not receive coverage from their employers highlights the politics involved in this crucial element of the new federal health care law.
lead_paragraph: An icy clash between Gov. Mark Dayton, a Democrat, and Republican lawmakers shows the politics involved in a crucial element of the new federal health care law.
